metadata.title: Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil
aws::graph::propositions: # Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil Accident History
A pilot of an Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil was able to free himself from a crashed helicopter.
The pilot was rescued by a nearby tugboat.
On 27 February 2019, an Air Dynasty AS350 B3e helicopter crashed shortly after takeoff.
The Air Dynasty AS350 B3e helicopter crashed in Taplejung, Nepal.
The Air Dynasty AS350 B3e helicopter crash killed all seven people on board.
Tourism and Civil Aviation Minister Rabindra Adhikari was among the seven people killed in the Air Dynasty AS350 B3e helicopter crash.
On 31 August 2019, an Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil crashed in the mountains of Skoddevarre.
Skoddevarre is located in Alta Municipality in northern Norway.
The Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil crash in Skoddevarre killed all six occupants.
In response to the Skoddevarre accident, Airbus made crash-resistant fuel systems part of the standard kit for the Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil.
Airbus made crash-resistant fuel systems standard on 1 October 2019.
On 7 March 2021, an Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil carrying Olivier Dassault crashed on takeoff near Deauville.
Deauville is located in Normandy, France.
There were no survivors in the Deauville Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil crash.
Olivier Dassault was a billionaire French politician and industrialist.
On 27 March 2021, an Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil carrying Petr Kellner crashed at Knik Glacier.
Knik Glacier is located in Alaska.
The Knik Glacier Eurocopter AS350 Écureuil crash killed five people.
Petr Kellner was a Czech billionaire.

text:
The pilot was able to free himself and was rescued by a nearby tugboat.
On 27 February 2019, an Air Dynasty AS350 B3e helicopter crashed shortly after takeoff in Taplejung, Nepal, killing all seven people on board, including Tourism and Civil Aviation Minister Rabindra Adhikari.
On 31 August 2019, an AS350 crashed in the mountains of Skoddevarre in Alta Municipality in northern Norway, killing all six occupants. In response to the accident, Airbus made crash-resistant fuel systems part of the standard kit for the aircraft on 1 October.
On 7 March 2021, an AS350 carrying billionaire French politician and industrialist Olivier Dassault crashed on takeoff near Deauville (Normandy) with no survivors.
On 27 March 2021, an AS350 carrying Czech billionaire Petr Kellner crashed at Knik Glacier (Alaska), killing five.
